						               													<description>The obelisks are rumored to exist in another place, a realm where time and space do not exist. They are thought to represent the very essence of purity and chaos. Within this indescribable place, beyond the dimensions of the infinite and eternal, unimaginable powers manipulate the obelisks, through extraplanar summoning, repositioning, and banishment. It is believed that some of these banished obelisks may be reformed, creating massive rifts between dimensions. This mysterious cycle is known as Obelus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Obelus is a light-weight abstract strategy game, playable in 10-15 minutes. Through the course of the game you will summon obelisk shaped dice onto the various conflux cards, move your obelisks according to the number showing, and banish your opponent&amp;rsquo;s obelisks. Banished obelisks may be reformed, but this creates a rift that prevents further summoning on that conflux. You win when your opponent has no legal move (or ability to summon) remaining!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
